**Abstract:**
Letter to Mary Lyn Stoll at Purdue University commenting on her paper on Kierkegaard and postmodernity. Praises her treatment of the difference between Kierkegaard and postmodern deconstructionists. Questions her understanding of indirect communication, suggesting it relates to truths requiring appropriation by decision. Confesses that indirect communication remains the obscurest aspect of Kierkegaard's thought for him.

**AI Recommendation:** Academic correspondence; reveals Monasterio's uncertainty about indirect communication.

